{"id":"243015895_Borel_Chromatic_Numbers","abstract":"We study in this paper graph coloring problems in the context of descriptive set theory. We consider graphs G=(X, R), where the vertex set X is a standard Borel space (i.e., a complete separable metrizable space equipped with its σ-algebra of Borel sets), and the edge relation R ⊆ X^2 is\n\"definable\", i.e., Borel, analytic, co-analytic, etc.\n\nA Borel n-coloring of such a graph, where 1⩽ n ⩽ N_0 , is a Borel map c: X → Y with card(Y)=n, such\nthat xRy⇒c(x) ≠ {c( y). If such a Borel coloring exists we define the Borel\nchromatic number of G, in symbols X_B(G), to be the smallest such n.\nOtherwise we say that G has uncountable Borel chromatic number, in symbols X_B(G) > N_0.","authors":["Alexander Kechris","Slawomir Solecki","S Todorcevic"],"meta":["January 1999Advances in Mathematics 141(1):1-44","DOI:10.1006/aima.1998.1771"],"references":["242915537_The_chromatic_number_of_the_product_of_two_1_-chromatic_graphs_can_be_countable","220441605_The_chromatic_number_of_the_product_of_two_Alef","322944008_A_Combinatorial_Construction_of_a_Nonmeasurable_Set","313627801_A_Glimm-Effros_dichotomy_for_Borel_equivalence_relations","303495897_Ergodic_equivalence_relations_cohomology_and_von_Neumann_algebras_I","278932463_2_EXAMPLES_OF_BOREL_PARTIALLY_ORDERED_SETS_WITH_THE_COUNTABLE_CHAIN_CONDITION","268650513_Combinatorial_Set_Theory","268635769_Countable_generators_in_dynamics_-_universal_minimal_models","266542095_Measurable_dynamics","266513261_Two_remarks_on_Ramsey's_theorem","266220186_On_chromatic_number_of_infinite_graphs","265991909_Ensembles_ordonnes_et_leurs_sous-ensembles_bien_ordonnes","265547821_A_Combinatorial_Construction_of_a_Nonmeasurable_Set","256391675_Arc_Colorings_of_Digraphs","248743169_Continuous_colorings_of_closed_graphs","248731915_Combinatorial_Set_Theory_Partition_Relations_for_Cardinals","244888225_Shift_graphs_and_lower_bounds_on_Ramsey_numbers_rkl_r","243771728_The_Structure_of_Hyperfinite_Bo